Direct Known Subclasses:
OsmEdgeStore
public abstract class EdgeStore extends ArchivedGraphElementStore<Edge> implements com.telenav.kivakit.core.registry.RegistryTrait
An efficient store of edge information used by the flyweight Edge object to retrieve attributes. A sequence of the edges in this store can be retrieved with edges(). The store is also Iterable because it inherits from GraphElementStore, so the "advanced" for loop can be used to process all the edges in the store. The existence of an edge in the store can be determined with contains(Edge).

When an edge is added to this store the onAdd(Edge) method is called. Adding the edge involves storing edge attributes with calls to several store* methods, as well as creating vertexes and storing connectivity information in the VertexStore. When edges are added, they can be fused together if merge(boolean) is set to true. This allows two graphs to be merged together into a coherent whole.

When edges are added to the store, only the forward edge is stored if the edge is two-way to increase storage efficiency. When edges are retrieved, a negative EdgeIdentifier signals that the data for the forward edge should be flipped around to return the reverse edge. Whether an edge is forward or reversed can be determined with Edge.isForward() and Edge.isReverse(). Because only forward edges are stored, the size of the store as returned by GraphElementStore.size() will be smaller than from the number of edges in the store as returned by count(). In some instances it is desirable to retrieve only the forward edges in the store. This can be achieved with forwardEdges().

A mapping is maintained between EdgeIdentifier and an index, which is stored as a property of each Edge (it is stored by the parent class GraphElement along with the edge's Graph and its GraphElementIdentifier). This index can be retrieved with GraphElement.index() and is used to efficiently retrieve values from the store with calls to the various retrieve* methods.

An edge store maintains an RTreeSpatialIndex of the edge poly-lines to allow fast spatial searches, such as finding all the edges that intersect a given Rectangle. This index is also used when querying EdgeRelations by finding the relevant edges and then returning the set of all relations that those edges reference.

This store Validatable so that it can be validated before saving to a GraphArchive with a call to validator(ValidationType). See Validatable and Validator for details of how validation works.
